data.text:
As a RS - Junior (2013):

- Missed the season opener with an injury, then started the next 11 contests at right tackle.

- In for a career-high 95 gradeable snaps versus Syracuse.

As a RS - Sophomore (2012):

- Started three games at left tackle early due to injuries, then moved to the starting right tackle spot and started the final nine games of the season there.

As a RS - Freshman (2011):

- Saw action from scrimmage in three games plus nine on special teams.

As a Freshman (2010):

- Redshirted the season.

In High School/Prep:

- Ranked the 12th best post graduate player in the country by Rivals.com.

- Started at defensive tackle for coach John Shuman at Fork Union Military Academy, he originally signed with State in 2009.

- Spent most of his high school career playing DL for coach Robert Lake.

- Senior Stats: 36 tackles, 14 tackles for loss. Had eight tackles, five TFL, two caused fumbles, and blocked an extra point in his final game.

- Junior Stats: 56 tackles, 22 tackle for loss, and nine sacks.

- First-team all-conference, all-county, all-area and all-state group-two as a junior and named to Prep Star's All-East Region class of 2009.
